          structure on your local machine that reflects the platform you're using. For example, you might
          create a folder on your C drive called "\GitHub\{username}\{repository}".  Then you can easily see
          which repositories have been cloned.
          This helps me keep track of where code is stored
          and avoid cluttering the file system with unorganized code.

